  "prompt": "Were any real sets built for The Lego movie?",
  "response": "The Lego Movie primarily utilized CGI (computer-generated imagery) to create the vibrant and intricate world made entirely out of LEGO bricks. The filmmakers made extensive use of realistic CG animation to mimic the appearance and movement of LEGO pieces, ensuring the film stayed true to the look and feel of actual LEGO sets. While real LEGO sets were not built for the scenes in the movie, every design was meticulously crafted to be consistent with what could be physically constructed using real LEGO bricks. This approach helped in making the animated LEGO world incredibly authentic and believable.",
